        <h2 id="mistakes" style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-top: 48px;">Common Beginner Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
        <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">Mistake 1: Buying Too Much Gear</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">New producers waste thousands on gear they don't need. Start minimal. Your skills matter 100x more than your equipment.</p>
        <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">Mistake 2: Tutorial Hell</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Watching endless tutorials without making music. Rule: For every hour of tutorials, spend 3 hours producing.</p>
        <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">Mistake 3: Not Finishing Tracks</h3>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Starting 50 tracks and finishing none. Force yourself to finish your first 10 tracks even if they're not perfect.</p>
      </section>

